cs.CG, cs.DM, cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.GR

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the geometric properties and algorithms for constructing simple orthogonal polyhedra.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also likely as the paper involves graph-theoretic characterizations of the polyhedra.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses efficient algorithms for constructing the polyhedra from their graphs.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is relevant as the paper involves characterizations of graphs of polyhedra.
- cs.GR (Graphics) is less likely as the paper does not focus on visualization or rendering of the polyhedra, but rather on their mathematical properties and algorithms.
